    <Heading>
    General Tips
    </Heading>
    <List>
    <ListItem>
    Use the least privilege necessary.
    </ListItem>
    <ListItem>
    Put up multiple roadblocks (defense in depth).
    </ListItem>
    <ListItem>
    Specify what you allow, not what you deny.
    </ListItem>
    <ListItem>
    Use secure defaults.
    </ListItem>    
    <ListItem>
    Don't rely on users to make good security decisions.
    </ListItem>
    <ListItem>
    Remember the human element - spoofing and social engineering.
    </ListItem>
    <ListItem>
    I'll say it again - don't trust anything that comes over the network.
    Verify all input. Assume all remote systems are hostile and out to steal the
    user's data.
    </ListItem>
    </List>
